JISC Capital Programme: Digitisation - Request for Proposals

The JISC Capital Programme, funded by HEFCE and=20
HEFCW from April 2006 =96 March 2009, consists of=20
six areas of development: Network; Digitisation;=20
Repositories; e-Learning; e-Infrastructure; and=20
User Environments. Further information about the=20
development areas can be found at:=20
<http://www.jisc.ac.uk/capital.html>http://www.jisc.ac.uk/capital.html

JISC has issued a Request for Proposals for=20
Digitisation Projects as part of the JISC Capital=20
Programme.  This Request for Proposals is aimed=20
primarily at enabling access, use and re-use=20
through the digitisation of analogue collections=20
for learning, teaching and research.  It is=20
envisaged that a small number of large scale=20
projects with a minimum budget allocation of=20
=A3500,000 will be funded through this=20
programme.  However, this guideline should not=20
discourage proposals from highly significant=20
educational and research collections that may require funding at a lower=
 level.

Proposals may be submitted by an institution,=20
organisation or consortia with collections of=20
significant value to higher education and research in England and Wales.

The deadline for proposals is 12 noon on Friday 26th May 2006.

A Digitisation Programme Town Meeting will be=20
held in London on Friday 21st April to discuss=20
this call.  The Town Meeting will consist of=20
presentations, parallel workshops on specific=20
issues relating to digitisation, expert panel=20
sessions and the opportunity to ask questions on=20
the new call for proposals. Further information=20
about the Town Meeting including an online=20
booking form can be found at:=20
<http://www.jisc.ac.uk/index.cfm?name=3Devent_digmtg_0406>http://www.jisc.ac=
.uk/index.cfm?name=3Devent_digmtg_0406

The full Request for Proposals is available on=20
the JISC website at:=20
<http://www.jisc.ac.uk/index.cfm?name=3Dfunding_capital_digitisation>http://=
www.jisc.ac.uk/index.cfm?name=3Dfunding_capital_digitisation


